&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 2.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Indolence&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means avoidance of activity or exertion; laziness. (आलस्य)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;His &lt;strong&gt;indolence&lt;/strong&gt; prevented him from completing his assignments on time.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Sloth&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to reluctance to work or make an effort; laziness. (आलस्य)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;Her &lt;strong&gt;sloth &lt;/strong&gt;in doing chores annoyed her roommates.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, we can infer that the synonym for &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Indolence&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Sloth&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Insufficiency&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;अपर्याप्तता&lt;/span&gt;): The condition of being not enough.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The insufficiency of funds led to the project&amp;#39;s cancellation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Embarrassment&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;शर्मिंदगी&lt;/span&gt;): A feeling of self-consciousness, shame, or awkwardness.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; He felt great embarrassment when he tripped on stage.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Involvement&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;भागीदारी&lt;/span&gt;): The fact or condition of being involved with or participating in something.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; Her involvement in community service is commendable.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Honarary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given question&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Honarary&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is an incorrectly spelt word&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
