&lt;p&gt;The recent economic downturn has led to a significant _____ in consumer spending.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Decline&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; means to become less in quantity, value, or power; to decrease or diminish.(गिरावट,&amp;nbsp;अवनति)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In the given sentence, due to&amp;nbsp;economic downturn&amp;nbsp;means worsening of conditions or circumstances, consumers are not spending freely.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;The&amp;nbsp;sales of the product have been steadily &lt;strong&gt;declining &lt;/strong&gt;in recent years.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the&lt;strong&gt; correct answer&lt;/strong&gt; is&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Decline&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meaning and example sentences.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Upsurge &lt;/strong&gt;(चढ़ाव,&amp;nbsp;उन्नति): A&amp;nbsp;sudden increase of something

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;The coronavirus pandemic has led to an &lt;strong&gt;upsurge &lt;/strong&gt;in remote work.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rebound &lt;/strong&gt;(उलट आना,&amp;nbsp;फिराव): To bounce back from a low point or setback; to recover from a fall or defeat.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;After losing the first game, the team made a strong &lt;strong&gt;rebound &lt;/strong&gt;and won the next three.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Escalation &lt;/strong&gt;(वृद्धि,&amp;nbsp;गहरा हो जाना): A gradual increase in intensity or seriousness.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;The ongoing border dispute between the two countries has &lt;strong&gt;escalated &lt;/strong&gt;into a full-scale war&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;desparate&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct spelling is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;desperate&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; which means &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;feeling or showing a hopeless sense that a situation is so bad as to be impossible to deal with.&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;महसूस करना या निराशाजनक भावना दिखाना कि स्थिति इतनी खराब है कि उससे निपटना असंभव है।&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Examples,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;I felt I couldn&amp;#39;t cope with the situation and was in &lt;strong&gt;desperate&lt;/strong&gt; need of some reassurance.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The earthquake survivors are in &lt;strong&gt;desperate&lt;/strong&gt; need of help.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, &lt;strong&gt;option 1&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct answer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Synonyms of the word&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;desperate&amp;#39;:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;despairing,&amp;nbsp;hopeless, anguished, distressed,&amp;nbsp;forlorn,&amp;nbsp;disheartened,&amp;nbsp;discouraged&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Antonyms of the word&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;desperate&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;: cheerful, composed,&amp;nbsp;happy&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the &lt;strong&gt;meaning &lt;/strong&gt;of the other words given in options:-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dependence &lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;the state of relying on or being controlled by someone or something else. (किसी पर या किसी और चीज पर निर्भर होने या नियंत्रित होने की अवस्था)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Discipline&lt;/strong&gt; -&amp;nbsp;the practice of training people to obey rules or a code of behaviour, using punishment to correct disobedience. (अनुशासन)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Delicious &lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;highly pleasant to the taste. (स्वादिष्ट)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To waste time on useless things.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The &lt;strong&gt;meaning&lt;/strong&gt; of idiom&lt;strong&gt; flogging a dead horse&lt;/strong&gt; is&amp;nbsp;squander energy on a lost cause or an unchangeable situation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The expression &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;beat a dead horse&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;comes from the mid-nineteenth century, when the practise of beating horses to make them run faster was widely accepted. It would be pointless to beat a dead horse because it would not be able to move.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt; :&amp;nbsp;She keeps trying to revive her dead relationship but I think she&amp;#39;s&lt;strong&gt; flogging a dead horse&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Some more&lt;strong&gt; idioms related to animals&lt;/strong&gt; are :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ants in your pants&lt;/strong&gt; - Being restless and moving around due to excitement or nervousness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example : I have got &lt;strong&gt;ants in my pants &lt;/strong&gt;today as we are going for a picnic after so long.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To smell a rat&lt;/strong&gt; - To be suspicious of a lie&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example : My mother was trying to&lt;strong&gt; smell a rat&lt;/strong&gt; when I told her my test got cancelled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Crocodile tears &lt;/strong&gt;- pretending or faking to cry to gain sympathy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example : Ria have a habit of shedding &lt;strong&gt;crocodile tears.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Post-mortem&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Post-mortem&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;means &amp;#39;a medical examination of a dead body to find out how the person died&amp;#39;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;For eg.-&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;postmortem&lt;/strong&gt; on the presidential campaign is under way.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus use the word &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;diagnosis&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; is&amp;nbsp;the most appropriate&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;one word &amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;for the given&amp;nbsp;expression.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 2&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the correct answer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Suicide:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;the act or an instance of taking one&amp;#39;s own life voluntarily and intentionally (स्वेच्छा से और जानबूझकर अपनी जान लेने की क्रिया या उदाहरण)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Homicide:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;a person who kills another (एक व्यक्ति जो दूसरे को मारता है)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Analysis:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;a careful study of something to learn about its parts, what they do, and how they are related to each other (किसी चीज़ के भागों के बारे में जानने के लिए, वे क्या करते हैं, और वे एक-दूसरे से कैसे संबंधित हैं, इसका सावधानीपूर्वक अध्ययन करना)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 3.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Mercenary&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means a soldier who fights for money rather than for a cause. (भाड़े का सैनिक)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The &lt;strong&gt;mercenary &lt;/strong&gt;was hired to protect the convoy through the dangerous terrain.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Mercenary&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;refers to someone who is primarily concerned with making money at the expense of ethics. (भाड़े का सैनिक)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; His &lt;strong&gt;mercenary&lt;/strong&gt; attitude made him unpopular among his colleagues.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 3.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Marine&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;समुद्री सैनिक&lt;/span&gt;): A member of a military force trained to serve on land and at sea.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The marine was deployed to assist in the coastal operations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Veteran&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;पूर्व सैनिक&lt;/span&gt;): A person who has served in the military.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The veteran shared his war experiences with the younger soldiers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Admiral&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;नौसेना अध्यक्ष&lt;/span&gt;): A high-ranking officer in the navy.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The admiral oversaw the entire fleet during the naval exercise.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
